<br>
Seriously, about the only &quot;good&quot; change that anyone seems to agree on (at least on the forums I've read) is the manaburn change. Maybe now I won't have to hear another tale like the one I got from a bard friend who, after several months of frustration, wound up having to trade his prized SS BP to a greedy manaburner for a stinkin' white scale. Yes, that actually happened on the Rathe.<br>
<br>
The CH changes, I can see the reasoning behind them. The execution of said changes is another matter. We'll just have to wait and see on that.<br>
<br>
The mod rod change is just a big fat nerf. There's no other way to describe it. About the best way I can think of to handle this is to have mages in the rotation channel with the clerics, so they can feed rods when needed. Mages need more changes than just nerfing mod rods to change their current role on raids, unfortunately.<br>
<br>
The CH change and mod rod nerf together were supposed to be part of eliminating the CH rotation. But Verant has IMHO missed the point. The mob's HP are not why rotations are needed. The mob's DPS is the problem. When a mob is quadding for three digits per hit, ESPECIALLY if the mob is unslowable, then chain healing is the only way to cover the damage. And the most efficient way to chain heal is in a rotation. Until Verant figures out a way to reduce mob DPS and still keep encounters challenging, healing rotations aren't going to go away.<br>
<br>
The monk change...*sigh*. I really hope Verant doesn't screw the execution of this up, because if they do it WILL kill the class. I am also concerned about how the changes to armor effectiveness will spill over to other leather and chain wearing classes. On the bright side, maybe this means that the plate wearing classes will start actually getting the protection that they're supposed to have.<br>
<br>
The bottom line is, this is all further evidence that I am not playing the same game that I started playing over three years ago. I really have to wonder if I'm actually playing EQ anymore, or if I'm just paying to beta-test concepts for EQ2.<br>
<br>
